In late September 2016 I bought a Ford F-150 (@fig-F150). This was one of the first versions of the aluminum bodied trucks. For that reason, and just out of curiosity, I kept data relative to every tank of gas that I have put into the truck.

A few results as of November 10, 2025.

- 112,781 miles driven (see @fig-ttlmiles)
- 5,930.3 gallons of gas purchased at a total of \$17,229.53 (see @fig-ttlgas and @fig-ttlgascost)
- The price of gas ranged from \$1.43 on April 24, 2020 to \$4.71 on June 24, 2022 (see @fig-cpgtank)
- Overall, averaged 19.0 miles per gallon (see @fig-avgmpgyr and @fig-mpgtank); 19.8 when not pulling anything

